<statement>
<p>Solve the equation: <m>\displaystyle{20}{\left({10}^{{-{9}{x}}}\right)}-{15}={0}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=</m><fillin characters="6" /> </p>
<p>Round to 3 decimal places.</p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>0.014</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{20}{\left({10}^{{-{9}{x}}}\right)}-{15}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{20}{\left({10}^{{-{9}{x}}}\right)}=-{15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}^{{-{9}{x}}}=-\frac{{15}}{{20}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}={\log{{\left(-\frac{{15}}{{20}}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{\log{{\left(-\frac{{15}}{{20}}\right)}}}}{{-{{9}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx{0.014}</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

